self.\n- The second, separate anomaly is that host_2 has no IPv4 address; it is currently offline from a network perspective and not participating in the network (DHCP not granted/received or interface misconfigured).\n- Devices implicated for the backend isolation: load_balancer (holds the 20.200.0.0 interface and is performing forwarding) and server_access_router/FRR (lack of advertisement/route for 20.200.0.0). The root cause is a routing/OSPF advertisement gap for the 20.200.0.0 network.\n- Devices implicated for the host_2 problem: host_2 (no IP) and possibly switch_access_2_1_1 or distribution DHCP-relay path (further troubleshooting required to localize precisely).\n\nNo remediation steps are given here (per request). If you want, I can now:\n- (a) produce a prioritized checklist of verification steps and targeted commands to confirm the root cause(s) (e.g., check OSPF LSDB and adjacency on core routers, check whether the load_balancer should advertise 20.200.0.0 or if server_access_router should have that network), or\n- (b) proceed to run more active probes/commands (FRR show ip ospf database, vtysh OSPF neighbor/state on core routers, ARP tables on server_access_router, tcpdump on load_balancer or server_access_router, or check switch port status for host_2) to further pinpoint the exact configuration error.\n\nWhich follow-up would you like?, please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.\nAI: \nTool: [\"dns_record_error\", \"host_crash\", \"host_ip_conflict\", \"host_incorrect_dns\", \"host_incorrect_gateway\", \"host_incorrect_ip\", \"host_incorrect_netmask\", \"host_missing_ip\", \"dhcp_service_down\", \"dns_service_down\", \"host_vpn_membership_missing\", \"link_detach\", \"link_down\", \"link_flap\", \"link_fragmentation_disabled\", \"arp_acl_block\", \"bgp_acl_block\", \"dns_port_blocked\", \"http_acl_block\", \"icmp_acl_block\", \"ospf_acl_block\", \"bgp_asn_misconfig\", \"bgp_blackhole_route_leak\", \"bgp_hijacking\", \"bgp_m